20/07/2003
BOURGAS, Bulgaria -- The mayors of Bourgas and the Albanian town of Vlora signed a memorandum of co-operation on Saturday (19 July). 
Meeting in Bourgas, Yoan Kostandinov and Niko Veizai discussed opportunities for co-operation between the two towns and benefits from implementation of the regional infrastructure project, Corridor 8. 
The Bulgarian hosts described the project to modernise and expand the Bourgas port. 
Veizai will also meet with the director of the Bourgas Trade and Industry Chamber to discuss the possibilities for co-operation in industry and tourism. 
(BTA - 19/07/03)
